[20:55] <disbot4> <librasteve> arnot: I would answer your question like this: (i) map and >> (hyper) are alternative ways to apply an operation to all items in an Array; (ii) each of them takes items from the array and applies an operation to it - so using them together is not advised

[20:56] <disbot4> <librasteve> arnot: hypers are meta operators - so the thing that is applied to each item is an operator, not a block (so your example block {$_ + 2} cannot be directly used via hyper syntax

[20:56] <disbot4> <librasteve> arnot: luckily you can make your own operators with Raku ;-)

